abla \cdot } \kappa \mathbf { B }$ activation mightbe mediated bya viral protein expressed duringHCV infection.Thus, we constructed a panel of expression plasmids that encoded the $1 0 \mathrm { H C V }$ proteins with N-terminal epitope tags and then used a luciferase reporter assay to screen for their ability to suppress TNF- $\mathbf { \sigma } \cdot \mathbf { a }$ -mediated NF- $\mathbf { \sigma } \cdot \mathbf { \kappa } \mathbf { B }$ activation.Transient transfection of HEK 293T cells with plasmids encoding P7,E1,E2,NS2,NS4A,NS4B,or NS5A proteins did not affect TNF $\mathbf { 
